 806   //   X* = X - (Y * |_ X / Y _|)
 807   //   R  = X* % Y
 808   // so we don't need the *first* iteration to return, we just need to
 809   // know *which* iteration will always return, so we could also rewrite it as:
 810   //   X* = X - (Y * |_ X / Y _|)
